<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-02T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-02T16:00:00-05:00" n="201" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94 Commission/60: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation to
                                the General Disarmament Conference (<persName corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-02T22:00:00+01:00">February 2, 1932—10
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received February 2—9:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>5. From <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">Wilson</persName>. <persName corresp="#p_GPB1">Gilbert</persName>’s 69, February 2, 2 p.m.<note n="37" xml:id="d201fn37">Not printed.</note>
                            <persName corresp="#p_DSE1">Drummond</persName> has received reply from
                            Shanghai which omits the names of members of Commission but states that
                            first meeting was held this afternoon and that all members are Consuls
                            General and that Italian is also Chargé d’Affaires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_GHS1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>